<h3>Tips to manage stress</h3>
						<ol>
							<li>If you often feel stressed or anxious, it's important to
								learn how to relax. This can allow you to take a step back from
								the stress Click on one of the following options to try one our
								guided relaxation (Script developed by KUL)
								<ul>
									<li>visualisation</li>
									<li>deep breathing</li>
								</ul>
							</li>
							<li>Physical activity, eating well and getting plenty of
								rest can all help you to feel less stressed.</li>
							<li>Make a list of things that help you to relax and
								schedule one every day.</li>
							<li>Identify situations that make you feel stressed at home
								or at work and try and work the problem out by talking things
								through before they become more of a problem.</li>
							<li>Change how you react to stressful situations- If you
								feel you can't change the stressful situation, try changing your
								attitude towards them.</li>
							<li>Challenging stressful thoughts- If you feel stressed and
								tense, or you feel frustrated, angry or depressed, take a step
								back.
								<ul>
									<li>Give yourself some space, remind yourself that getting
										stressed won't help, and take a couple of minutes to think
										about what you can do to change your situation.</li>
								</ul>
							</li>
							<li>If you have negative thoughts going through your mind -
								like 'I can't cope', or 'I'm useless' - try challenging them
								with more positive thoughts, like 'I know I will get through
								this in time' or 'there are lots of things I am good at'.
						</ol>
